  "body": "### Description\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: When new chat is created and I press the back button, I get redirected to the new chat screen. I'd expect to be redirected to Home tab instead. \r\nNote that it also happens for chats that are already on the list but were reopened by selecting them from the new chat screen.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nA user is redirected to Home tab when pressing back button in the chat screen.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nA user is redirected to the previous screen she was on - New Chat. It seems logical but it's not intuitive (UX). \r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Create new chat\r\n- Press back button\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: Android, iOS\r\n* Operating System: nightly, April 12",
